node.text:
Do 4 rounds of this and tell me how you feel😅

Sled push
Walking lunges
Kettle swings
BACK TO BACK!

1 min rest between rounds.

The best feeling I get, is after these workouts.

node.text:
During my isolation it was tough not being able to gym, but had to find the motivation to get some type of sweat in so I came up with a few workouts, so here’s a good one! try this if you’re stuck in the house or if your gym isn’t open!

-30 sec jump rope
-30 sec in and out squat jumps
-30 sec RDL to squat
-30 sec lunge up jumps
-30 sec alt side plank twists

Wearing my own @get_tighterr sweat belt to make me feel tight and to sweat a little extra durning my HIIT workouts 😁 you can pre order yours with the link in my bio! 
Sizes S-XXL (true to size)
I’m wearing a medium

node.text:
You can tell yourself it’s impossible but You’d be telling yourself a lie 🤷🏽‍♀️

I’m telling you, I NEVER believed I could lose weight, I remember telling my self every summer before school started, I’d actually try to lose weight but I never even tried 😬

I don’t know what lit the fire but once it was lit, it never died. The feeling over being over 300 lbs is enough motivation to never go back 🤟🏽
———-
I can’t tell you exactly what to do because everyone’s body is different but I definitely can say, you can’t fail if you don’t try.

If you need a guid for an at home workout program click the link in my bio! Minimal equipment, 4 weeks, demonstration to every exercise and beginner friendly!

Raise your hand If you like a good cardio sweat 🙋🏽‍♀️

We’re launching a new limited series of my belts since last run ran out!! Shipping day starts October 1st! So if you didn’t get yours you’ll be able to order and receive it next month 😁

I wear a size medium, for your size reference- measurements are on @get_tighterr website!

This belt is not for losing weight, I only use this to keep me feeling tight during high intensity workouts and of course to sweat a little extra💧

node.text:
I gave myself 2 weeks to eat what ever I wanted, sweets, French fries, pizza, you name it, I ate it. Food is BIG comfort for me.

What do I want to do when I have a little anxiety? Eat.

What do I want to do when I’m feeling down? Eat.

What do I want to do when I’m bored? Eat.

When my mom was in the hospital and we were playing the waiting game, and after hearing the news.. All I wanted to do was cry, I didn’t care what I put in my body.

I allowed myself to just feel all the emotions (which I still am) and I didn’t have any control on my healthy lifestyle. I told myself after Labor Day, I was going to get back to focus mode and not let myself eat my feelings. It’s only been a few days but I feel so much better. It’s one thing to feel sad but another to feel sad AND uncomfortable in my body.

My mom wouldn’t want me to give up so I will keep going and I will keep making her proud. 🤟🏽🙏🏽💪🏽

Outfit - @stori ✨

node.text:
You’re the only one who can make excuses for yourself. Don’t make them 🤷🏽‍♀️

If you need guidance on a home workout click the link in my bio and check out my 4 wee at home program!
 
This program is designed for anyone looking for guidance on getting a good workout in without a gym.

If you have dumbbells and resistance bands you’re all set! 💪🏽

-4 weeks consisting of 
•abs everyday
•HIIT warm up
•2 upper body days
•2 lower body days
•1 full body day
•recovery stretches 

Each exercise in the program is performed so you understand how to do it.
